d from this setting via the mechanism of SO coupling. Collisions between\nthe pair of these two types of solitary modes are also discussed in the paper.\nThe pair of the 0H solitary mode features only the elastic collision, whereas\nthe pair of 1H solitary modes can feature both elastic and inelastic collision\nwhen the total energy flow of the two modes are smaller or close to the\nthreshold norm of the \\emph{Townes soliton}.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 10 Dec 2017 14:54:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-09"}
